### Custom Subdomain Redirection Controllers
1. **[CentralRegisteredUserController.php](file:///c:/Users/Z.BOOK/Desktop/things/code/web-builder/app/Http/Controllers/Auth/CentralRegisteredUserController.php)**: 
   - Handles guest user registration.
   - Generates a unique, URL-safe tenant subdomain deterministically from the user's name.
   - Automatically initializes a default `home` page with starting canvas components.
   - Redirects to `http://{subdomain}.domain.localhost/editor` using `Inertia::location`.
2. **[CentralAuthenticatedSessionController.php](file:///c:/Users/Z.BOOK/Desktop/things/code/web-builder/app/Http/Controllers/Auth/CentralAuthenticatedSessionController.php)**:
   - Validates user credentials.
   - Implements standard security rate-limiting matching the test suite's expectations.
   - Redirects to the tenant's editor subdomain if a workspace is present, or defaults to the central management panel.
   - Destroys active sessions on sign out.

### Routing & Configuration
1. **[web.php](file:///c:/Users/Z.BOOK/Desktop/things/code/web-builder/routes/web.php)**: Split routing using `Route::domain()` structures, assigning unique route names (`central.login` and `central.register`) to avoid Wayfinder TypeScript generated duplicates.
2. **[.env](file:///c:/Users/Z.BOOK/Desktop/things/code/web-builder/.env)** & **[.env.example](file:///c:/Users/Z.BOOK/Desktop/things/code/web-builder/.env.example)**: Set `SESSION_DOMAIN=.domain.localhost` to enable cross-subdomain sessions, and mapped `CENTRAL_DOMAIN=domain.localhost`.

